race.comment: PRIVATE EYE (3) looks very well placed in the second running of the Supernova. He's off a let-up for this having been tested in the Russell Balding last time, running another honest race when fifth to Jimmysstar which is the best 1400m form in the country. He's largely been kept away from the top horses this time in and its paid dividends. This is a strong race but there aren't any bona fide stars and he looks the one to beat. HERE TO SHOCK (1) was very well ridden to take the Listed Testa Rossa at Caulfield in a bounce back to form. He did win this race last year and should acquit himself very well. ZOU SENSATION (8) continues to race well in a long campaign. He tried hard after settling off speed in the Meteorite and his best figures are at 1400m when he can dictate which looks the case here. ARKANSAW KID (4) beat him home there and has claims although 1400m is as far as he wants. WARNIE (5) beat ZOU SENSATION at Flemington and the run last time was good, he'll be strong late.
